title: Fighting Spirit: Wheeling Diggers' Invictus Games Dream
episode_name: Fighting Spirit: Wheeling Diggers' Invictus Games Dream
description: This deeply moving documentary goes behind-the-scenes of the Invictus Games Sydney 2018 to follow the formation of Australia's wheelchair rugby team as they struggle to reclaim their lives on and off the court.

title: Fightback Farmers
description: Facing the challenge of a lifetime, Australian farmers and fishers are banding together in a modern take on an old way of working together. Their goal is to save family farms from corporate takeover and protect a way of life.

title: Australia Debates
description: The funniest minds in Australia debate the findings of three issues uncovered by the Australia Talks national survey, asking 60,000 Australians 600 questions, and come to their own conclusions.
description2: ['Tom Cashman, Demi Lardner and Nat Damena argue the case that Pets are Better than People, against Mel Buttle, Dane Simpson and Lizzy Hoo arguing the negative. Moderated by Nikki Britton.', "Arj Barker, Vidya Rajan and Suren Jayemanne argue the case that Younger Australians Have it Easier These Days, against Fiona O'Loughlin, Bridie Connell and Michael Hing arguing the negative. Moderated by Nikki Britton.", 'Steph Tisdell, Sam Campbell and Veronica Milsom argue the affirmative case that Social Media Should be Banned - against Nina Oyama, Danielle Walker and Blake Freeman arguing the negative. Moderated by Nikki Britton.']

title: The Crown and Us: The Story of The Royals in Australia
description: The Crown is part of who we were and who we are - and despite the secrets, scandals and questions of relevance, our reverence for the British Royals remains as strong as ever. Why is that? And will it ever change?
description2: ['Explore the relationship between Australia and the Crown from 1954 through to the election of Gough Whitlam as Prime Minister in 1972.', "Do we need a British monarch as our head of state? A look at Australia's relationship with the Crown from 1974 to now, through Royal secrets, scandals and the impact of Princess Diana. (Final)"]
features: crown part despite secret scandal question relevance reverence british royal remains strong ever ever change
